'''''Bobby Kennedy for President''''' is an American documentary television series that focuses on Senator [[Robert F. Kennedy|Robert Kennedy]] and his political rise in the 1960s.<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/entertainment/archive/2018/04/bobby-kennedy-for-president-review-netflix/559010/|title='Bobby Kennedy for President' Captures an Awkward Icon|last=Gilbert|first=Sophie|date=2018-04-30|work=The Atlantic|access-date=2018-09-17|language=en-US}}</ref> The four-part first series was released on [[Netflix]] on April 27, 2018.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://variety.com/2018/tv/news/robert-f-kennedy-netflix-bobby-kennedy-for-president-documentary-1202728214/|title=Netflix Nabs 'Bobby Kennedy for President' Documentary Series (EXCLUSIVE)|last=Morfoot|first=Addie|date=2018-03-16|work=Variety|access-date=2018-09-17|language=en-US}}</ref>

The series, [[Showrunner|run]] by director and executive producer [[Dawn Porter (filmmaker)|Dawn Porter]], looks at Kennedy's political lore, including his 1968 presidential campaign, which ended with [[Assassination of Robert F. Kennedy|his assassination]] on June 5, 1968.<ref name=":0" /> The show uses archival footage during Kennedy's time as Attorney General and Senator, as well as conversations he had with his brothers, President [[John F. Kennedy]] and Senator [[Ted Kennedy]].<ref name=":2">{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2018/04/26/entertainment/bobby-kennedy-review/index.html|title='Bobby Kennedy for President' adds to rich trove of Kennedy lore|last=Lowry|first=Brian|date=April 26, 2018|work=CNN|access-date=2018-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/bobby-kennedy-president-review-1105428|title='Bobby Kennedy for President': TV Review|last=Fienberg|first=Daniel|date=April 25, 2018|work=The Hollywood Reporter|access-date=2018-09-17|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/04/26/arts/television/review-bobby-kennedy-for-president-netflix.html|title=Review: In 'Bobby Kennedy for President,' a Don Draper of Politics|last=Hale|first=Mike|date=April 26, 2018|work=The New York Times|access-date=2018-09-17|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/27/bobby-kennedy-netflix-documentary-shines-a-light-on-his-relevance|title=Bobby Kennedy: Netflix documentary shines a light on his relevance|last=Holpuch|first=Amanda|date=2018-04-27|website=the Guardian|language=en|access-date=2018-09-17}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.thrillist.com/entertainment/nation/bobby-kennedy-for-president-netflix-documentary-review|title=Netflix's Bobby Kennedy Documentary Reveals Stark, Tragic Truths About An American Political Dynasty|last=Campbell|first=Christopher|date=April 27, 2018|work=Thrillist|access-date=2018-09-17}}</ref>

In addition to archival footage, the show interviews dozens of individuals who, at one point, were in Kennedy's circle, including Rep. [[John Lewis (civil rights leader)|John Lewis]], [[Dolores Huerta]], [[Harry Belafonte]], [[Marian Wright Edelman]], and [[William vanden Heuvel]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2" />

