A '''one in, one out policy''' is a method used to control the number of people in one place or building at any one time.  Where a place or building has reached its maximum [[seating capacity|capacity]], further entry is only allowed upon a person leaving.  It is especially used in [[nightclub]]s and [[Bar (establishment)|bar]]s, and most [[military]] establishments.

